excerpt: Desert art museum with European & Native American works, plus a theater, outdoor space & cafe.
detail_description: The Palm Springs Art Museum is a desert oasis for art enthusiasts, offering a diverse collection of European and Native American works. The museum's cool interior provides respite from the desert heat, with captivating exhibitions that range from Picasso retrospectives to architectural showcases. Visitors can enjoy free admission on select days, making it an accessible cultural experience. Nestled against the picturesque San Jacinto Mountains, the museum houses an ever-evolving display of modern and contemporary art by Western and Native American artists.
name: Palm Springs Art Museum
address: 101 N Museum Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Rotating tram cars travel through Chino Canyon to a station with dining, a museum & hiking trails.
detail_description: The Palm Springs Aerial Tramway offers a unique experience, taking visitors on a scenic journey through Chino Canyon to the mountain station. The tram cars rotate as they ascend over 1 mile, providing breathtaking views of the Coachella Valley and its nine cities. Once at the mountain station, visitors can explore Mount San Jacinto State Park with its 50 miles of hiking trails, observation decks, natural history museum, and documentary theaters.
name: Palm Springs Aerial Tramway
address: 1 Tramway Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Historic landmark opened in 1938 featuring a desert environment with guided tours & a nursery.
detail_description: Moorten Botanical Garden, a historic landmark established in 1938, is a hidden gem in Palm Springs. It showcases over 3,000 varieties of desert plants and cacti, some of which are exclusive to this garden. The one-acre estate was built by Chester Moorten and his wife Patricia and serves as a living museum of desert allure.
name: Moorten Botanical Garden
address: 1701 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

excerpt: Museum dedicated to combat aircrafts from WWII to present years, plus art, a gift shop & a cafe.
detail_description: The Palm Springs Air Museum, established in 1996, is a sprawling museum dedicated to combat aircraft from WWII to the present day. It boasts one of the world's largest collections of flyable and static WWII aircraft, including iconic planes like the Boeing B17 Flying Fortress and the Grumman F-14 Tomcat.
name: Palm Springs Air Museum
address: Parking, lot 745 N Gene Autry Trail, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: This group of canyons has trails for hiking & horseback riding, plus picnic areas & a gift shop.
detail_description: Indian Canyons, located in the mountain foothills of Palm Springs, is a collection of canyons that hold great cultural and historical significance as the ancestral home of the Agua Caliente Band of Cahuilla Indians. Visitors can explore Tahquitz Canyon with its guided hikes to a 60-foot waterfall, Andreas Canyon featuring unique rock formations and lush plant life, and Murray Canyon where lucky hikers might spot endangered Peninsular Big Horn Sheep.
name: Indian Canyons
address: 38520 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

excerpt: Canyon with a waterfall, rock art, plants & wildlife, along with a visitor center.
detail_description: Tahquitz Canyon is a stunning natural wonder in Palm Springs with ancient rock art, wildlife, and lush vegetation. It's a popular destination for hikers and picnickers who can enjoy the scenery, along with a visitor center that provides information about the area's history.
name: Tahquitz Canyon
address: 500 W Mesquite Ave, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

detail_description: N Palm Canyon Dr is a bustling thoroughfare in the heart of Palm Springs, lined with various accommodations and attractions. One such establishment is the Hyatt Palm Springs, located right downtown on this vibrant street. Staying at this hotel offers an incredible experience as it situates guests in the midst of all the action and excitement that Palm Springs has to offer.
name: N Palm Canyon Dr
address: California 92262, USA

excerpt: Resource for maps, postcards, gifts & logo clothing in an iconic former tramway station.
detail_description: The Palm Springs Visitor Center is housed in the iconic former tramway station, a striking glass-and-steel landmark with a space-age profile and triangular roofline. Designed by architects Albert Frey and Robson Chambers, the building features a soaring, wing-like roof known as a "hyperbolic paraboloid." Inside, visitors can find maps, postcards, gifts, and logo clothing while learning about accommodations, activities, dining options, and hiking opportunities in the greater Palm Springs area.
name: Palm Springs Visitor Center
address: 2901 N Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Palm Springs, a city in the Sonoran Desert of southern California, is known for its hot springs, stylish hotels, golf courses and spas. It's also noted for its many fine examples of midcentury-modern architecture. Its core shopping district along Palm Canyon Drive features vintage boutiques, interior design shops and restaurants. The surrounding Coachella Valley offers hiking, biking and horseback riding trails.
detail_description: Palm Springs, located in the Sonoran Desert of southern California, is renowned for its hot springs, chic hotels, golf courses, and spas. The city boasts a plethora of midcentury-modern architecture and a vibrant shopping district along Palm Canyon Drive with vintage boutiques and dining options. In the surrounding Coachella Valley, visitors can explore hiking, biking, and horseback riding trails.
name: Palm Springs
address: California, USA

detail_description: Villagefest Main Office Palm Springs is a popular weekly event that takes place every Thursday night, where the street is closed to traffic and filled with vendor booths showcasing local businesses. Visitors can enjoy strolling through the traffic-free event, sampling food, exploring art, and enjoying live music. The fair offers a wide variety of authentic handmade arts and crafts for sale. Many visitors highly recommend this lively and enjoyable evening activity in Palm Springs, featuring great food and shopping opportunities for everyone.
name: Villagefest Main Office Palm Springs
address: 401 S Pavilion Way, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Sidewalk plaques & statues honoring local celebrities amid a busy pedestrian scene.
detail_description: The Walk of the Stars in Palm Springs is a tribute to the many Hollywood celebrities who have lived and enjoyed this desert oasis since the 1920s. The sidewalk features plaques, handprints, and signatures of famous actors, musicians, and other celebrities. Lined with majestic palm trees and sparkling lights, Palm Canyon Drive offers art galleries, restaurants, pubs, and shops. Thursday nights are especially lively with VillageFest featuring vendor booths and a traffic-free environment for strolling.
name: Walk of the Stars Palm Springs
address: 10 N Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Modern wind turbine farm with educational tours dedicated to wind energy.
detail_description: Palm Springs Windmill Tours offers an educational and exciting experience for families to learn about wind energy in the Coachella Valley. Located in the windy San Gorgonio Pass just outside Palm Springs, visitors can witness the impressive wind turbines up close and gain valuable insights into renewable energy sources and their role in a sustainable future. The tours provide eye-opening educational resources for families, transforming their understanding of environmental conservation.
name: Palm Springs Windmill Tours
address: 62950 20th Ave, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

detail_description: The Palm Springs Art Museum is home to a diverse collection of art from different centuries, including contemporary works by California artists, classic western and Native American art, Mesoamerican and Mexican art, European modern art, glass studio art, mid-twentieth century American architecture, and photography. The museum boasts 28 galleries, two sculpture gardens, a lecture hall, gift store, bistro, and Annenberg Theater.
name: Palm Springs Art Museum Architecture and Design Center
address: 300 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Lively, palm-lined strip offering restaurants, galleries, shops & museums, plus street festivals.
detail_description: S Palm Canyon Dr is a vibrant boulevard adorned with palm trees, featuring an array of dining spots, art galleries, retail outlets, and museums. The street comes alive with various street festivals, offering a lively atmosphere for visitors. Just south of the Palm Springs Airport lies Indian Canyons, an enchanting location known for its family-friendly hiking trails. This reserve welcomes the public to explore and appreciate the stunning natural landscapes with children in tow.
name: S Palm Canyon Dr
address: California, USA

excerpt: Historic house museum in a 35-room Hopi-style pueblo featuring Native American art & artifacts.
detail_description: Cabot's Pueblo Museum is a historic house museum located in Desert Hot Springs, featuring a 35-room Hopi-style pueblo that showcases an extensive collection of Native American art and artifacts. The museum was hand-built by Cabot Yerxa, an adventurer and artist, in the 1940s. It also houses Yerxa's own artwork, handiwork, and souvenirs from his travels. The site offers a unique cultural experience with its maze-like structure and rich history.
name: Cabot's Pueblo Museum
address: 67616 Desert View Ave, Desert Hot Springs, CA 92240, USA

detail_description: Every Thursday night transforms into a vibrant celebration at VillageFest, where the streets come alive as they close to traffic. This delightful event features an array of vendor booths lining both sides of the street, inviting visitors to leisurely wander through and soak in the lively atmosphere. It's a perfect opportunity to explore unique offerings while enjoying a pleasant evening out!
name: Villagefest
address: 100 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Cathedral City, colloquially known as "Cat City", is a desert resort city in Riverside County, California, United States, within the Colorado Desert's Coachella Valley. Situated between Palm Springs and Rancho Mirage, the city has the second largest population, after Indio, of the nine cities in the Coachella Valley. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Cathedral City, also known as "Cat City," is a popular desert resort destination located in Riverside County, California. Nestled in the Colorado Desert's Coachella Valley between Palm Springs and Rancho Mirage, it is the second most populous city in the area. Welk Resorts Desert Oasis provides ample and inviting lodging for families, featuring a pool area ideal for enjoyable family time and a variety of organized activities for kids.
name: Cathedral City
address: California, USA

excerpt: Smithsonian-affiliated museum showcasing Cahuilla Indian history with exhibits, lectures & classes.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant downtown Palm Springs, the Agua Caliente Cultural Museum invites visitors to immerse themselves in the rich tapestry of Cahuilla Indian history. This Smithsonian-affiliated museum serves as a gateway to understanding the traditions and customs of the Agua Caliente Band of Cahuilla Indians, who have thrived in this desert landscape for millennia. Guests can explore an array of exhibits that feature traditional artifacts alongside contemporary artwork, all designed to honor and celebrate the enduring legacy of these indigenous people.
name: Agua Caliente Cultural Museum
address: 140 N Indian Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Lively Downtown Palm Springs is a compact hub that draws crowds with eclectic shops, the Walk of Stars, and the Palm Springs Art Museum, home to 2 sculpture gardens and a performing arts theater. Farm-to-table bistros, classic Italian restaurants, and bars with live music and drag shows bring evening crowds, while weekly night market VillageFest has stalls with art, vinyl, gourmet foods, and crafts.
detail_description: Downtown Palm Springs is a vibrant and compact area that attracts visitors with its diverse range of attractions. The Palm Springs Art Museum, featuring sculpture gardens and a performing arts theater, is a major draw. The district also boasts an array of dining options, from farm-to-table bistros to classic Italian eateries, as well as bars offering live music and drag shows. Additionally, the weekly night market VillageFest showcases art, gourmet foods, and crafts.
name: Downtown Palm Springs
address: Palm Springs, CA, USA

excerpt: Stylish eatery for inventive New American eats & seasonal craft cocktails in a former movie house.
detail_description: Workshop Kitchen & Bar is a stylish restaurant housed in a former movie house, located within the beautifully renovated 1920s colonial El Paseo building. The dining room features an elegant and minimalist design with high ceilings, concrete walls, and a long communal table surrounded by cozy booths.
name: Workshop Kitchen & Bar
address: 800 N Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Old-school supper club hosting intimate music & comedy shows accompanied by a surf 'n' turf menu.
detail_description: The Purple Room Supper Club is a classic establishment that originally opened in 1960 and was frequented by celebrities like Frank Sinatra and Dean Martin. Under the ownership of entertainer Michael Holmes, it offers an intimate dining experience with live jazz, pop, and cabaret performances. The venue hosts music and comedy shows while serving a surf 'n' turf menu.
name: Purple Room Supper Club
address: 1900 E Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

name: Tahquitz Falls
address: Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

detail_description: Start your day with a reservation for an early morning hike to Tahquitz Falls within the Agua Caliente Indian Reservation. The well-maintained trails offer a chance to explore native wildlife and ancient irrigation systems before the desert temperatures begin to soar. The seasonal 60-foot waterfall is a rewarding sight at the end of the hike.
name: Agua Caliente Indian Reservation
address: Palm Springs, CA, USA

detail_description: The Elvis Honeymoon Hideaway, also known as the House of Tomorrow, is a serene and secluded spot located just five minutes northwest of downtown. This beautiful building served as the honeymoon home for Elvis and Priscilla Presley. The estate is an excellent example of mid-century modernism with its unique circular layout across three floors. Designed by Robert Alexander, it was featured in Look Magazine in 1962 and has been meticulously restored to showcase its stunning design details.
name: Elvis Honeymoon Hideaway
address: 1350 Ladera Cir, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

detail_description: The Palm Springs Aerial Tramway offers an unforgettable experience as it transports visitors from the desert floor to the breathtaking heights of Mount San Jacinto State Park. This scenic ride spans over two and a half miles, providing stunning panoramic views of the Coachella Valley and surrounding mountains. As you ascend, you'll witness a remarkable change in scenery, transitioning from arid desert landscapes to lush alpine forests.
name: Palm Springs Aerial Tramway
address: 1 Tramway Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Desert Hot Springs is a city in Riverside County, California, United States. The city is located within the Coachella Valley geographic region. The population was 32,512 as of the 2020 census, up from 25,938 at the 2010 census. The city has experienced rapid growth since the 1970s when there were 2,700 residents. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Desert Hot Springs, located in Riverside County, California, is a city that has seen significant growth since the 1970s. Situated within the Coachella Valley region, it had a population of 25,938 as of the 2010 census. The area offers various outdoor activities such as hiking and exploring desert landscapes.
name: Desert Hot Springs
address: California, USA

detail_description: The Tonga Hut Restaurant and Tiki Bar is a vibrant and colorful establishment located in Palm Springs, with a rich history dating back to 1958. The decor features traditional tiki bar elements such as thatched roofs, bamboo accents, and glowing tiki torches. The menu offers an array of inventive cocktails and tasty Polynesian cuisine, including meat-skewer pu-pu platters served on carved wood dishes.
name: The Tonga Hut Restaurant and Tiki Bar
address: 254 N Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Tequila & Mexican street food served in a rustic, stylish cocktail bar at The Saguaro Palm Springs.
detail_description: El Jefe Desert Cantina is a vibrant and stylish cocktail bar located at The Saguaro Palm Springs, offering a lively atmosphere and serving up Mexican street food such as cochinita pork and chicken tinga tacos. The cantina also features regional desserts like date bread pudding. With a diverse menu that includes vegan, meat, and seafood options for their tortilla fillings, El Jefe provides an authentic Mexican dining experience.
name: El Jefe Desert Cantina
address: 1800 E Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

excerpt: Scenic mountain range & state park with soaring peaks, sweeping views, campsites & hiking trails.
detail_description: Nestled in California, Mount San Jacinto State Park offers a diverse landscape of soaring peaks and breathtaking vistas. The weather undergoes a dramatic shift from the Coachella Valley floor to the top of the aerial Tramway in Palm Springs, providing a refreshing change for visitors. Hiking enthusiasts can explore an array of trails, including the renowned Pacific Crest Trail and routes leading to Mt. San Jacinto.
name: San Jacinto Mountains
address: California, USA

excerpt: This non-profit features 2 19-century buildings with history exhibits, plus walking tours.
detail_description: The Palm Springs Historical Society operates 2 19th century buildings which feature interesting history exhibits. The McCallum Adobe is the oldest building in Palm Springs and features wall placards with information about famous players of old Palm Springs. The Golden Era Hollywood Home tour is highly recommended and the staff is very knowledgeable about local history.
name: Palm Springs Historical Society
address: 221 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

detail_description: The Sonny Bono Statue in downtown Palm Springs pays tribute to the multifaceted career of the late musician, actor, and mayor. The statue captures him in his iconic pose, reflecting his enduring impact on the community. Visitors can strike a pose with the statue and explore other nearby attractions like the Walk of Fame. For a peaceful photo opportunity, consider visiting early in the morning when the streets are quiet and you can fully appreciate Palm Springs' diverse motifs.
name: Sonny Bono Statue
address: 155 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: 430-seat theater at the Palm Springs Art Museum hosting diverse live performances & film screenings.
detail_description: The Annenberg Theater, located within the Palm Springs Art Museum, is a 430-seat venue known for its diverse live performances and film screenings. The theater's nearly perfect acoustics and state-of-the-art facilities have earned it praise from audiences who return year after year to enjoy events like the International Palm Springs Film Festival. With well-padded seats and excellent visibility of the large screen from any seat, visitors can also explore three floors of art at the museum before or after a show.
name: Annenberg Theater
address: 101 N Museum Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Large, quirky yard with sculpture & light displays combining sci-fi & religious holiday themes.
detail_description: Robolights is a fascinating and quirky yard filled with colorful sculptures and light displays that blend sci-fi and religious holiday themes. The captivating garden features larger-than-life creations made from recycled materials, resembling props from a high-budget Hollywood sci-fi movie. Created by Kenny Irwin, the garden showcases an array of otherworldly artifacts such as plastic aliens, a UFO parking sign, and giant robotic arms. Visitors are drawn to this unique attraction to marvel at the imaginative artwork displayed throughout the property.
name: Robolights
address: 1077 E Granvia Valmonte, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Airport serving Southern California & featuring a playground as well as free WiFi.
detail_description: Palm Springs International Airport is a gateway to Southern California, offering amenities like a playground and free WiFi. The city of Palm Springs has a population of around 49,000 and boasts an LGBTQ-identified local government. Known as a historic gay oasis, it has attracted celebrities since the early 20th century. Today, it offers sun, swimming, parties, hip hotels, fabulous eateries, clothing-optional gay resorts, and stunning views of the San Jacinto mountains.
name: Palm Springs International Airport
address: 3400 E Tahquitz Canyon Way, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Vast, eclectic menu of all-day American eats presented in a modern setting with outdoor seating.
detail_description: Lulu California Bistro is a popular dining spot in Palm Springs, known for its vast and diverse menu of American cuisine served all day. The restaurant has received accolades such as being voted Best of in various categories by Desert Magazine readers and recognized as one of the Top 100 Dining Hot Spots by OpenTable. With a modern setting and outdoor seating, Lulu offers a lively atmosphere for breakfast, lunch, Sunday brunch, or dinner, along with a 12-hour Happy Hour.
name: Lulu California Bistro
address: 200 S Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Stylish, industrial-chic eatery serving ambitious riffs on Vietnamese fare, plus craft cocktails.
detail_description: Rooster And The Pig is a trendy restaurant in Palm Springs that offers a unique twist on Vietnamese cuisine with a Southern California influence. The industrial-chic eatery, owned by Chef Tai Spendley, serves up creative dishes like arancini with a panko crust and chicken stuffing, as well as aromatic coconut yellow curry. The bar menu includes an array of beverages from beers and wines to specialty cocktails and non-alcoholic options like Vietnamese iced coffee.
name: Rooster And The Pig
address: 356 S Indian Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Cool Ace Hotel diner offering an eclectic Cal-Mexican menu highlighting locally sourced ingredients.
detail_description: King's Highway is a trendy diner located at the Ace Hotel & Swim Club, housed in a restored Denny's with a touch of quirky California cool. The menu features an eclectic Cal-Mexican selection made from locally sourced ingredients, including original vegetarian-friendly dishes and classic favorites like burgers. The ambiance is enhanced by unique decor elements such as stained glass windows and flagstone walls. The attached bar, Amigo Room, offers frozen cocktails and hosts Monday night bingo.
name: King's Highway
address: 701 E Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

excerpt: Playful bar offering rum-filled cocktails, happy-hour deals & a patio decorated with tiki torches.
detail_description: Bootlegger Tiki is a vibrant bar located in the original Don the Beachcomber building, featuring playful Polynesian decor and an array of rum-filled cocktails. The bar's attention to detail is evident in its drinks, which are often adorned with orchids, herbs, and umbrellas. Guests can savor unique concoctions like the allspice and green chartreuse-infused pina colada or the gin-based Northwest with lime, celery bitters, and rosemary.
name: Bootlegger Tiki
address: 1101 N Palm Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Low-key eatery offering an all-vegetarian menu of deli sandwiches & salads plus healthy bowls.
detail_description: Chef Tanya's Kitchen is a low-key eatery that offers an all-vegetarian menu featuring deli sandwiches, salads, and healthy bowls. Founded by chef Tanya Petrovna, who previously established the first national vegan chain, Native Foods, the restaurant specializes in plant-based dishes made with house-made ingredients like kale giardiniera, tofu "facon," and chickpea "tuNO."
name: Chef Tanya's Kitchen
address: 706 S Eugene Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

detail_description: The Palm Springs International Film Festival, now in its 25th year, is a must-see event for film enthusiasts. The festival showcases approximately 325 short films from around the world in themed programs at Camelot Theatres. It's an opportunity to witness diverse and premiering movies. Additionally, the International Bear Convergence attracts bears and their admirers for a four-day extravaganza of pool parties and dance events.
name: Palm Springs International Film Festival
address: 303 N Indian Canyon Dr Floor 3, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Bustling casino open 24/7 with a music venue & a sports bar, plus a cafe & a steakhouse.
detail_description: Located just one block away from PSCC, Agua Caliente Casino Palm Springs is a bustling 24/7 casino offering slots, table games, and high-limit gaming. The stylish yet comfortable setting includes a live music lounge and various downtown experiences such as shopping and dining at The Block. This sparkling casino also features a private live poker room in an upscale atmosphere, making it a player's paradise.
name: Agua Caliente Casino Palm Springs
address: 401 E Amado Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Ingleside Inn's longtime eatery has American fare, old Hollywood history & a lounge with live music.
detail_description: Nestled within the historic Ingleside Inn, Melvyn's is a renowned eatery with a rich Hollywood legacy. The restaurant offers classic American cuisine and hosts a lively lounge featuring live music, often accompanied by a pianist. This establishment exudes an old-school charm that attracts a diverse crowd, from seniors to younger patrons and even bachelorette parties. The piano players are known for their extensive repertoire, catering to various musical tastes and prompting guests to hit the small dance floor.
name: Melvyn's at the Ingleside Estate
address: 200 W Ramon Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

excerpt: Visitor information for the local area is available from these offices providing essential services.
detail_description: Greater Palm Springs is a collection of nine cities, each with its own unique attractions and charm. While Palm Springs is a standout destination with its iconic mid-century modern architecture and vibrant dining and shopping scene, the entire region offers plenty to explore. Visitors can find essential services and visitor information at local offices, as well as robust online event calendars from the Palm Springs Bureau of Tourism and The Greater Palm Springs Convention and Visitors Bureau. For LGBTQ travelers, there are dedicated resources available, including guides and business listings.
name: Greater Palm Springs
address: 70100 CA-111, Rancho Mirage, CA 92270, USA

excerpt: Boutique hotel in a mid-century modern home with an outdoor pool & stylish, desert-inspired decor.
detail_description: The Amado is a charming boutique hotel set in a serene residential area at the heart of Palm Springs. This mid-century modern home features five units, each with its own kitchen and living room, exuding stylish desert-inspired decor. Guests can unwind by the outdoor pool surrounded by fragrant citrus trees.
name: The Amado
address: 1821 E Amado Rd, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

detail_description: The Oasis Music Festival is an annual event that features performances by some of the most renowned artists from around the world. Held in California, this festival has gained a reputation as one of the largest and most popular music festivals in the region. With its seasonal schedule, it offers attendees a chance to experience top-tier musical acts and immerse themselves in an unforgettable atmosphere.
name: Oasis Music Festival
address: 303 N Indian Canyon Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Many trails & an aerial tram lead to the summit of this 10,000-ft. mountain with panoramic views.
detail_description: Mount San Jacinto, standing at 10,000 feet, offers a variety of trails and an aerial tram that lead to its summit, providing breathtaking panoramic views. The Palm Springs Aerial Tramway Hike is a popular way to reach the peak with less effort compared to other routes. The summit provides a unique vantage point where the transition between Coastal California and the Sonoran Desert ecosystems can be observed.
name: Mount San Jacinto
address: California, USA

excerpt: Celebrities, such as Frank Sinatra, are buried in this scenic, serene cemetery established in 1956.
detail_description: Nestled in Cathedral City, Desert Memorial Park is a tranquil resting place that has been welcoming visitors since its establishment in 1956. This serene cemetery is home to the final resting spots of iconic figures like Frank Sinatra and Sonny Bono, making it a poignant destination for fans and locals alike. During my recent visit, I took a leisurely drive to this peaceful park, where I paid my respects not only to Sinatra but also to other notable personalities such as Busby Berkeley and William Asher.
name: Desert Memorial Park
address: 31-705 Da Vall Dr, Cathedral City, CA 92234, USA

excerpt: Center comprised of art galleries offering paintings, jewelry & ceramics, plus framing services.
detail_description: Nestled in Palm Springs, the Backstreet Art District is a vibrant hub of artistic expression. This neighborhood is filled with art galleries offering a diverse range of artworks including paintings, sculptures, jewelry, ceramics, and more by locally and internationally recognized artists. Visitors can witness artists at work in their studios and engage with them to gain insights into their creative process. The monthly First Wednesday Art Walk offers an opportunity to explore the district's offerings while enjoying the lively atmosphere.
name: Backstreet Art District
address: 2600 Cherokee Way, Palm Springs, CA 92264, USA

detail_description: Frey House II, nestled in the San Jacinto Mountains and now part of the Palm Springs Art Museum, is a testament to architect Albert Frey's innovative vision. Completed in 1964, this mid-century modern masterpiece seamlessly blends into its rocky surroundings. The house features a unique design with a natural boulder incorporated into its interior, dividing the living area from the bedroom.
name: Frey House II
address: 686 Palisades Dr, Palm Springs, CA 92262, USA

excerpt: Trails wind through this park at the peak of Mount San Jacinto, accessible by tram via Palm Springs.
detail_description: Mount San Jacinto State Park is a hiker's paradise located at the peak of Mount San Jacinto, accessible by tram from Palm Springs. The park offers 54 miles of diverse trails suitable for all levels of hikers, from leisurely strolls to challenging treks. One popular trail is the 2.5 mile Round Valley hike, known for its stunning views and serene surroundings.
name: Mount San Jacinto State Park
address: 25905 CA-243, Idyllwild-Pine Cove, CA 92549, USA
